(8, 'Farming in Italy', 'farming-in-italy', 15000.00000000, 15.00000000, 5, 1000.00000000, 25.00000000, 3750.00000000, '2024-09-11', '2024-10-10', 25, '2026-11-10', 2, 2, 2, 0, 25, 1, 1, '66d2b2224188d1725084194.jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?q=Rupur+Paromanobik+Kendro&key=AIzaSyBFw0Qbyq9zTFTd-tUY6dZWTgaQzuU17R8', '<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-family: Lato, &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: x-large; font-weight: 700; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">About This Project</span></div><ol style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: decimal; color: rgb(8, 9, 14); font-family: Lato, &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Crops:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Wheat and Barley:</span>&nbsp;Italy is a significant producer of wheat and barley, which are essential grains in Italian cuisine.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Corn (Maize):</span>&nbsp;Corn is widely cultivated, especially in the northern regions of Italy.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Viticulture:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Wine Production:</span>&nbsp;Italy is renowned globally for its wine production. The country has numerous wine regions, each producing distinct varieties, including Tuscany, Piedmont, Veneto, and Sicily.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Olive Oil Production:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Italy is one of the world’s largest producers of olive oil. Regions like Tuscany, Umbria, and Puglia are famous for their high-quality olive oils.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Cheese Production:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Parmesan (Parmigiano-Reggiano):</span>&nbsp;Emilia-Romagna is known for Parmesan cheese production.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Gorgonzola, Pecorino, and Mozzarella:</span>&nbsp;Other regions contribute to the production of renowned cheeses like Gorgonzola, Pecorino, and Mozzarella.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Fruits and Vegetables:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Italy produces a wide variety of fruits and vegetables, including tomatoes, artichokes, citrus fruits, and grapes for table consumption and processing.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Truffle Farming:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Piedmont and Umbria are known for truffle hunting and cultivation. Truffles, particularly white truffles, are highly valued in Italian cuisine.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Rice Cultivation:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">The Po Valley in northern Italy is known for rice cultivation, particularly for varieties like Arborio and Carnaroli used in traditional Italian dishes such as risotto.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Cattle Farming:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Chianina Cattle:</span>&nbsp;Tuscany is home to Chianina cattle, a breed known for producing high-quality beef.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Buffalo Farming:</span>&nbsp;Campania is known for buffalo farming, which contributes to the production of buffalo mozzarella.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Poultry and Egg Production:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Italy is a significant producer of poultry, including chickens and ducks. Egg production is also a vital aspect of the poultry industry.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Agricultural Regions:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Different regions of Italy specialize in specific agricultural products. For example, Emilia-Romagna is known for its dairy and meat production, while Sicily is renowned for citrus fruits.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Sustainable Agriculture:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Many Italian farmers are adopting sustainable and organic farming practices to promote environmental conservation and produce high-quality, natural foods.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">Agriturismo:</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Agriturismo, or farm stays, is a popular form of agritourism in Italy. Visitors can stay on working farms, experience rural life, and enjoy locally produced food and wine.</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside decimal;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: 700;\">EU Common Agricultural Policy (CAP):</span><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0.166667rem; padding-left: 20px; border: 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-type: disc;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; list-style: outside disc;\">Italy, as a member of the European Union, follows the Common Agricultural Policy (CAP), which supports and regulates agricultural activities across the EU member states.</li></ul></li></ol><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; backface-visibility: hidden; margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(8, 9, 14); font-family: Lato, &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Farming in Italy is not only an economic activity but also a cultural and culinary tradition deeply rooted in the country’s history. The diverse agricultural practices contribute to Italy’s reputation as a gastronomic paradise, and many visitors are drawn to the authentic experiences offered by Italian farms.</p>', '{\"0\":\"66d2bfd986f8e1725087705.jpg\",\"1\":\"66d2bfd98abb11725087705.jpg\",\"3\":\"66d2d7cbc869f1725093835.png\",\"4\":\"66d2d7cbe4bc91725093835.png\"}', 1, NULL, '2024-08-30 22:50:58', '2024-09-15 03:27:17'),
(9, 'Agriculture in Bangladesh', 'role-of-agriculture-in-bangladeshs-economic-growth', 15000.00000000, 25.00000000, 8, 600.00000000, 11.00000000, 1650.00000000, '2024-08-30', '2024-08-30', 11, '2025-07-30', 2, 3, 2, 0, 10, 1, 1, '66d2a71bd5c6a1725081371.jpg', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?q=Rupur+Paromanobik+Kendro&key=AIzaSyBFw0Qbyq9zTFTd-tUY6dZWTgaQzuU17R8', '<span style=\"color: rgb(16, 24, 40); font-family: &quot;Noto Serif JP&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px;\">After independence, the agriculture sector was Bangladesh\'s main economic driving force. Its contribution to GDP was around 60 percent. Agriculture in Bangladesh is vital for people\'s livelihood, employment, and contributing to GDP; we all know that. Its contribution has reduced over the last decade, going from 17 percent in 2010 to 12.6 percent in 2020. The sector is at the centre of our economy, decreasing poverty and ensuring food security. However, with the ever-growing population, going from 147.6 million in 2010 to 164.7 million in 2020, added by the blow of the pandemic and climate change, the sector has continued to be resilient in terms of profitability and productivity.</span><br>', '[\"66de88a16497f1725860001.jpg\",\"66de88a178a601725860001.jpg\",\"66de88a17c4991725860001.jpg\",\"66de88a17fec61725860001.jpg\"]', 1, NULL, '2024-08-30 23:00:56', '2024-09-10 07:06:46'),
(10, 'Invest in Baby Popcorn Field', 'invest-in-baby-popcorn-field', 20000.00000000, 10.00000000, 7, 2000.00000000, 10.00000000, 2000.00000000, '2024-09-09', '2024-06-09', 1, '2024-07-09', 1, 1, 2, 0, 10, 1, 2, '66dea4bd6fe651725867197.png', 'https://www.google.com/maps/@23.8698828,90.3842619,15z?entry=ttu', '<p>Popcorn may seem like a simple snack, but it\'s quickly becoming a powerhouse investment opportunity. With global demand for healthy, affordable snacks on the rise, popcorn has emerged as a favorite choice for consumers. From gourmet flavors to organic, non-GMO varieties, the popcorn market has diversified, attracting health-conscious individuals, foodies, and casual snackers alike.</p><p>This trend is reflected in the numbers. The global popcorn market is projected to reach over $15 billion by 2026, driven by increasing snack consumption and the growing popularity of home entertainment. As consumers seek healthier alternatives to traditional chips and candy, popcorn offers a low-calorie, high-fiber option that satisfies cravings without the guilt.</p><p>Investing in popcorn means tapping into a lucrative, expanding market with room for growth in production, packaging, and innovative product lines. Whether you\'re considering shares in established brands or exploring opportunities with emerging artisanal producers, the popcorn industry offers a range of options for investors looking to diversify their portfolios.</p><p>In this blog, we\'ll explore the trends driving the popcorn boom, key players in the industry, and why investing in popcorn could be a smart move for the future. Discover why this timeless snack is popping off in the world of business and investment!</p>', '[\"66dea4bdac61b1725867197.png\",\"66dea4bdc28b01725867197.png\",\"66dea4bdd74771725867197.png\",\"66dea4bded5921725867197.png\"]', 1, '{\"image\":\"66deee6b51a311725886059.png\",\"description\":\"Meta Description\",\"social_title\":\"The Water Development Board (WDB) initiated the \\\"Rejuvenating River Ichamati\\\" project with a budget of Tk 1554.90 crore.\",\"social_description\":\"The Water Development Board (WDB) initiated the \\\"Rejuvenating River Ichamati\\\" project with a budget of Tk 1554.90 crore.\",\"keywords\":[\"meta\",\"invest\",\"agri firm\"]}', '2024-09-09 01:33:18', '2024-09-10 07:09:58'),
